The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index dropped 889.86, or 3
percent, to 29,288.86 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg, its
biggest retreat since Aug. 8.  Anglo American Platinum Ltd. (AMS SJ): The worldâ€™s largest
platinum producer continues wage negotiations with the  National
Union of Mineworkers . The stock dropped 2.3 percent to 549 rand.  Brimstone Investment Corp. (BRT SJ): The investment-holding
company said earnings per share for the six months to June will
be as much as 45 percent lower than the prior period. Shares in
the company ended unchanged at 9 rand.  PSV Holdings Ltd. (PSV)  : The technology company withdrew
a cautionary announcement, saying conditions relating to its
disposal of its Group Line subsidiary have been met. The stock
rose 31 percent to 17 cents.  Trustco Group Holdings Ltd. (TTO)  : The property
development and financial services group holds its annual
general meeting. The shares were unchanged at 84 cents.  Vunani Ltd. (VUN)  : The financial-services company holds
its annual general meeting. The stock closed unchanged at 6
